		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">1. correctness of raster effect code</div><br />As long as the effects are not triggered by mapper IRQs.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">2. look of graphics on a TV, and 3. control feel on a gamepad.</div><br />Yeah, me too.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">3gengames wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">It's so worth it, I'm getting one one day.</div>
<br />It's totally worth it, I never said it wasn't. I use it for testing my own software all the time, much more than playing pirated games. I was just pointing out that it isn't the perfect development tool, because of all the CF card swapping, the fact that you don't get the untouched boot state and the few issues with mapper emulation (mostly related to IRQs).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
